        <div class="c-article-body">
            <section aria-labelledby="Abs3" data-title="Abstract" lang="en"><div class="c-article-section" id="Abs3-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="Abs3">Abstract</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="Abs3-content"><p>How to image objects that are hidden from a camera’s view is a problem of fundamental importance to many fields of research<sup><a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 1" title="Freund, I. Looking through walls and around corners. Physica A 168, 49–65 (1990)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR1" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e318">1</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 2" title="Wang, L., Ho, P. P., Liu, C., Zhang, G. &amp; Alfano, R. R. Ballistic 2-D imaging through scattering walls using an ultrafast optical Kerr gate. Science 253, 769–771 (1991)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR2" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e321">2</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 3" title="Huang, D . et al. Optical coherence tomography. Science 254, 1178–1181 (1991)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR3" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e324">3</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 4" title="Bertolotti, J. et al. Non-invasive imaging through opaque scattering layers. Nature 491, 232–234 (2012)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR4" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e327">4</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 5" title="Katz, O., Heidmann, P., Fink, M. &amp; Gigan, S. Non-invasive single-shot imaging through scattering layers and around corners via speckle correlations. Nat. Photon. 8, 784–790 (2014)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR5" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e330">5</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 6" title="Katz, O., Small, E. &amp; Silberberg, Y. Looking around corners and through thin turbid layers in real time with scattered incoherent light. Nat. Photon. 6, 549–553 (2012)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR6" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e333">6</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 7" title="Strekalov, D. V., Sergienko, A. V., Klyshko, D. N. &amp; Shih, Y. H. Observation of two-photon “ghost” interference and diffraction. Phys. Rev. Lett. 74, 3600–3603 (1995)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR7" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e337">7</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 8" title="Bennink, R. S., Bentley, S. J. &amp; Boyd, R. W. “Two-photon” coincidence imaging with a classical source. Phys. Rev. Lett. 89, 113601 (2002)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR8" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e340">8</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 9" title="Sen, P. et al. Dual photography. ACM Trans. Graph. 24, 745–755 (2005)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR9" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e343">9</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 10" title="Bouman, K. L . et al. In IEEE 16th Int. Conference on Computer Vision 2270–2278 (IEEE, 2017); &#xA;                    http://openaccess.thecvf.com/content_iccv_2017/html/Bouman_Turning_Corners_Into_ICCV_2017_paper.html&#xA;                    &#xA;                  " href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR10" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e346">10</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 11" title="Klein, J., Peters, C., Martin, J., Laurenzis, M. &amp; Hullin, M. B. Tracking objects outside the line of sight using 2D intensity images. Sci. Rep. 6, 32491 (2016)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR11" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e349">11</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 12" title="Chan, S., Warburton, R. E., Gariepy, G., Leach, J. &amp; Faccio, D. Non-line-of-sight tracking of people at long range. Opt. Express 25, 10109–10117 (2017)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR12" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e352">12</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 13" title="Gariepy, G., Tonolini, F., Henderson, R., Leach, J. &amp; Faccio, D. Detection and tracking of moving objects hidden from view. Nat. Photon. 10, 23–26 (2016)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR13" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e356">13</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 14" title="Kirmani, A ., Hutchison, T ., Davis, J. &amp; Raskar, R. In IEEE 12th Int. Conference on Computer Vision 159–166 (IEEE, 2009); &#xA;                    http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/5459160/&#xA;                    &#xA;                  " href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR14" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e359">14</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 15" title="Velten, A. et al. Recovering three-dimensional shape around a corner using ultrafast time-of-flight imaging. Nat. Commun. 3, 745 (2012)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR15" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e362">15</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 16" title="Buttafava, M., Zeman, J., Tosi, A., Eliceiri, K. &amp; Velten, A. Non-line-of-sight imaging using a time-gated single photon avalanche diode. Opt. Express 23, 20997–21011 (2015)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR16" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e365">16</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 17" title="Gupta, O., Willwacher, T., Velten, A., Veeraraghavan, A. &amp; Raskar, R. Reconstruction of hidden 3D shapes using diffuse reflections. Opt. Express 20, 19096–19108 (2012)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR17" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e368">17</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 18" title="Wu, D. et al. In Computer Vision – ECCV 2012 (eds Fitzgibbon, A., et al.) 542–555 (Springer, 2012); &#xA;                    https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-642-33718-5_39&#xA;                    &#xA;                  " href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR18" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e371">18</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 19" title="Tsai, C.-Y ., Kutulakos, K. N ., Narasimhan, S. G. &amp; Sankaranarayanan, A. C. In Proc. IEEE Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition 7216–7224 (IEEE, 2017); &#xA;                    http://openaccess.thecvf.com/content_cvpr_2017/html/Tsai_The_Geometry_of_CVPR_2017_paper.html&#xA;                    &#xA;                  " href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR19" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e375">19</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 20" title="Heide, F ., Xiao, L ., Heidrich, W. &amp; Hullin, M. B. In Proc. IEEE Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition 3222–3229 (IEEE, 2014); &#xA;                    http://openaccess.thecvf.com/content_cvpr_2014/html/Heide_Diffuse_Mirrors_3D_2014_CVPR_paper.html&#xA;                    &#xA;                  " href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR20" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e378">20</a></sup>, with applications in robotic vision, defence, remote sensing, medical imaging and autonomous vehicles. Non-line-of-sight (NLOS) imaging at macroscopic scales has been demonstrated by scanning a visible surface with a pulsed laser and a time-resolved detector<sup><a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 14" title="Kirmani, A ., Hutchison, T ., Davis, J. &amp; Raskar, R. In IEEE 12th Int. Conference on Computer Vision 159–166 (IEEE, 2009); &#xA;                    http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/5459160/&#xA;                    &#xA;                  " href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR14" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e382">14</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 15" title="Velten, A. et al. Recovering three-dimensional shape around a corner using ultrafast time-of-flight imaging. Nat. Commun. 3, 745 (2012)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR15" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e385">15</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 16" title="Buttafava, M., Zeman, J., Tosi, A., Eliceiri, K. &amp; Velten, A. Non-line-of-sight imaging using a time-gated single photon avalanche diode. Opt. Express 23, 20997–21011 (2015)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR16" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e388">16</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 17" title="Gupta, O., Willwacher, T., Velten, A., Veeraraghavan, A. &amp; Raskar, R. Reconstruction of hidden 3D shapes using diffuse reflections. Opt. Express 20, 19096–19108 (2012)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR17" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e391">17</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 18" title="Wu, D. et al. In Computer Vision – ECCV 2012 (eds Fitzgibbon, A., et al.) 542–555 (Springer, 2012); &#xA;                    https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-642-33718-5_39&#xA;                    &#xA;                  " href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR18" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e394">18</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 19" title="Tsai, C.-Y ., Kutulakos, K. N ., Narasimhan, S. G. &amp; Sankaranarayanan, A. C. In Proc. IEEE Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition 7216–7224 (IEEE, 2017); &#xA;                    http://openaccess.thecvf.com/content_cvpr_2017/html/Tsai_The_Geometry_of_CVPR_2017_paper.html&#xA;                    &#xA;                  " href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR19" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e397">19</a></sup>. Whereas light detection and ranging (LIDAR) systems use such measurements to recover the shape of visible objects from direct reflections<sup><a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 21" title="Schwarz, B. LIDAR: mapping the world in 3D. Nat. Photon. 4, 429–430 (2010)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR21" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e401">21</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 22" title="McCarthy, A. et al. Kilometer-range, high resolution depth imaging via 1560 nm wavelength single-photon detection. Opt. Express 21, 8904–8915 (2013)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR22" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e404">22</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 23" title="Kirmani, A. et al. First-photon imaging. Science 343, 58–61 (2014)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR23" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e407">23</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 24" title="Shin, D. et al. Photon-efficient imaging with a single-photon camera. Nat. Commun. 7, 12046 (2016)" href="/articles/nature25489#ref-CR24" id="ref-link-section-d16337094e410">24</a></sup>, NLOS imaging reconstructs the shape and albedo of hidden objects from multiply scattered light. Despite recent advances, NLOS imaging has remained impractical owing to the prohibitive memory and processing requirements of existing reconstruction algorithms, and the extremely weak signal of multiply scattered light. Here we show that a confocal scanning procedure can address these challenges by facilitating the derivation of the light-cone transform to solve the NLOS reconstruction problem. This method requires much smaller computational and memory resources than previous reconstruction methods do and images hidden objects at unprecedented resolution. Confocal scanning also provides a sizeable increase in signal and range when imaging retroreflective objects. We quantify the resolution bounds of NLOS imaging, demonstrate its potential for real-time tracking and derive efficient algorithms that incorporate image priors and a physically accurate noise model. Additionally, we describe successful outdoor experiments of NLOS imaging under indirect sunlight.</p></div></div></section>
